                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/east-230d1" class="program-course-title">
              EAST 230D1 First Level Chinese (4.5 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22028" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: East Asian Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Asian Language &amp; Literature              : Introduction to the basic structures of Mandarin Chinese, Pin-yin romanization and 750 characters for reading and writing. Emphasis on developing aural and oral skills through communication games and interaction activities. Animated films are used as part of teaching materials.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Renzhong Wang (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Students must register for both EAST 230D1 and EAST 230D2.</li>
              <li>No credit will be given for this course unless both EAST 230D1 and EAST 230D2 are successfully completed in consecutive terms</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
