                <h4>East Asian Literature, Culture and Society</h4>

    
              <p>21-24 credits of courses in East Asian Literature, Culture and Society selected from the list below.  At least 6 credits must be taken at the 400 or 500 level.</p>
    
      
      
                <h4>East Asian Studies (EAST)</h4>

    
      
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/east-215" class="program-course-title">
              EAST 215 Introduction to East Asian Art (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22016" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: East Asian Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Asian Language &amp; Literature              : Introductory survey of some of the major developments in the visual arts of Japan, China, and Korea.  Emphasis will be placed on the diversity of artistic traditions in East Asia and the intersections among these traditions.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Jeffrey Moser (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students taking or who have taken ARTH 215.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
