                <h4>Economics (ECON)</h4>

    
      
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/econ-335" class="program-course-title">
              ECON 335 The Japanese Economy (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22378" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Economics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Economics (Arts)              : The first part of the course covers the economic institutions in, changing structure of, and public policies employed by the Japanese economy. The second part probes the economic "logic" of the Japanese capitalist system, explores its relationship to the ideas of Joseph Schumpeter, and makes comparisons with the American economy.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        John C Kurien (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisites: ECON 208 and ECON 209 or those listed under Prerequisites above </li>
