                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/relg-442" class="program-course-title">
              RELG 442 Pure Land Buddhism (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-35071" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Religious Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Religious Studies              : The concept of Buddha Countries and Pure Lands in Buddhism, the Western Pure Land of Amida (Jodokyo) and its basic scriptures, the Chinese Buddhist schools, the introduction to Japan and the foundation of the Pure Land school by Honen, the Pure Land School of Shinran and its development, and the other Pure Land related schools.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        G Hori (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: RELG 252 and RELG 253, or RELG 342 or RELG 344, or permission of instructor </li>
            </ul>
      </div>

